        <type>s32</type>
        <definition>s32 XTtcPs_SetOptions</definition>
        <argsstring>(XTtcPs *InstancePtr, u32 Options)</argsstring>
        <name>XTtcPs_SetOptions</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_ttc_ps" kindref="compound">XTtcPs</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Options</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sets the options for the TTC device. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_ttc_ps" kindref="compound">XTtcPs</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Options</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>contains the specified options to be set. This is a bit mask where a 1 means to turn the option on, and a 0 means to turn the option off. One or more bit values may be contained in the mask. See the bit definitions named XTTCPS_*_OPTION in the file <ref refid="xttcps_8h" kindref="compound">xttcps.h</ref>.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if options are successfully set.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE if any of the options are unknown.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
